      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The window uses a buffer, but draws directly to the screen where possible and to the buffer for obscured portions."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You should typically not use this mode. It combines the limitations of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgwindowbackingtype/kcgbackingstorenonretained"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " with the memory use of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgwindowbackingtype/kcgbackingstorebuffered"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". The original NeXTSTEP implementation was an interesting compromise that worked well with fast memory mapped framebuffers on the CPU busâ€”something that hasn't been in general use since around 1994. These tend to have performance problems."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In macOS 10.5 and later, requests for retained windows will result in the window system creating a buffered window, as that better matches actual use"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
